{"key":"processedPost-13157954","value":{"id":13157954,"first":13154874,"last":13160767,"when":1283841038,"utime":"09/07/10 09:30 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />I haven't found a tek yet on proper fruiting/misting/faeing and that for me has to be the toughest part. </blockquote><br />There isn't one.&nbsp; It's why I recommend against using humidifiers with a terrarium.&nbsp; You'll end up flooding the darn thing and then performance will be poor or nil.&nbsp; If you have a shotgun terrarium sitting in an open room, and it's elevated on blocks so air can enter the bottom, you really don't need to fan at all.&nbsp; However, since fresh air causes evaporation of moisture from the substrate, which is the number 1 pinning trigger, it never hurts to fan it out now and then.<br />Misting should be done by hand using your eyeballs.&nbsp; There's no 'rule' for how often to mist.&nbsp; You mist as required.&nbsp; Use a very bright window or fluorescent lights during the daytime.<br />Growing mushrooms is only part science.&nbsp; The other part is an art form.&nbsp; What works is what works, thus when you learn to get great yields and few contamination problems, you'll be doing it right, whatever method you use.<br />RR","title":"Re: Fuck this hobby! Pathetic Harvest. Hard Work. Non Existant Trip. Need Help."}}